title: The Good Squirrel - helping local community with unique emergency prep service
description:
We help customers ensure that they always have appropriate food, water and supplies on hand in the case of an emergency. We regularly rotate out food before it expires and donate it to a food bank. (As you may have guessed, "squirrel" is in the name because squirrels are known for storing food for when it's needed in the future.) Here's our full description:
We know you want to be prepared to care for your family if a disaster strikes. Here in the bay area, we’ve traditionally prepared for earthquakes, but more recently we’ve also seen disruptions from rolling blackouts, the pandemic (including long lines at grocery stores) and supply chain slow-downs. We’ve all learned first-hand that anything can happen and we’d like to not be caught off guard.
We know that experts recommend that you have a week’s worth of food to get you through an emergency. The problem is that buying food that we may or may not use is time-consuming and feels wasteful. You may have avoided thinking about it altogether and feel guilty about not being prepared.
We understand. We’ve dragged our feet buying food for our disaster kits because it felt so wasteful to throw out perfectly good food year after year (if we even bothered to check it!) or buy food that lasts for 25 years that no one will want to eat.You deserve a fast and efficient way to create and manage your emergency food supply so you’ll be prepared with enough food, while ensuring none of it will go to waste.
That is why we created a turnkey membership service for disaster preparedness that's easy, efficient and socially responsible. We deliver real food customized for your family’s needs at regular intervals. When it’s time to refresh your food supply, we donate your previous food to your local food bank for you.
Here’s how we do it:
1. Become a member and tell us how many in your household and how many days you want to be prepared for.
2. Choose the day and we deliver your food to your door.
3. Every six months, we deliver a new food supply, donate your previous delivery to your local food bank and give you the receipt for your tax deduction.
4. Congratulations! Your family is disaster prepared with real food and no waste, AND you’re helping others with food insecurity.
Stop worrying your family won’t be prepared! Become a member today and enjoy a turnkey disaster preparedness solution that’s simple, waste-free, and enables you to generously provide for people with food insecurity. It’s a win for you and for your community.
other_notes: I’m mainly interested in a wordmark logo, although I'd consider logos with some graphical elements which may include a squirrel or acorn - or whatever ideas you have! The logo will mainly be used on our website. Screen shots of the home page are attached. The "Be Prepared" in the top nav will be replaced with the new logo. We can change the dimensions of the top navigation bar somewhat if needed.
